Reasoning: The paper discusses the role of research excellence, specifically measured by Web of Science publications, in the tenure assessment process in Chinese higher education institutions. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), cybersecurity (cs.CY), cryptography (cs.CR), and social and information networks (cs.SI). However, since the paper focuses on the evaluation of research output, cs.DL and cs.IR are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.CY, cs.CR, and cs.SI.
